    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="487"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d487">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/950.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 12, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department must know the exact text of the loan agreement and the coupon note
                    or bond before finally agreeing to the contracting <pb facs="0566" n="462"
                        xml:id="pg_462"/> of the loan. If the contract is the one already
                    communicated through the Department, cable any differences that may exist in the
                    text as signed from the text as cabled to you; if it is some other form of
                    contract, cable full text; also cable text of coupon note or bond.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
